name: Kumendel Rumah Makan Keluarga
address: Jl. Nanas, Kecicang, Pertigaan Terminal, GHWW+MGW, Subagan, Kec. Karangasem, Kabupaten Karangasem, Bali 80813, Indonesia
review 1: Nice and clean warung. Reasonably priced for having nice design/fixtures. Con: No Wi-Fi, no credit cards, busy street.
review 2: When we got there there was nobody at the tables. We asked for three things, after 15-20 minutes they brought only 2. I had to go to them to ask for the missing one. They brought it after 10 more minutes. Also, we asked no spicy but both squid and prawn skewers were spicy. Overall the taste was ok but service was not.
review 3: This is a family restaurant. Everyone can choose which one they like. Indonesian foods and combination with some Western foods. Easy parking for your car. Very good services from all the staffs. Good taste and The Price are very competitive. Please come and try this restaurant,if you come to this area.
review 4: Complete menu variant, good taste and the most important one: great value. Nasi goreng for 15K, fried/grilled chicken complete package for 32K. Not to mention the cozy atmosphere
review 5: Searched dinner place around Candidasa but finally we headed to Amlapura. We tried Gurame Nyat Nyat, a carp cooked with Balinese spices. Delicious! The carp accompanied with plecing (water spinach and sprouts topped with sambal and peanut). Love the fried prawns too. Very nice ambiance with some plantations. We'd love to come back someday and try others what they offers.
